[
  {
    "start": 0.0,
    "text": "I like kimchi. I love the kimchi. I love it."
  },
  {
    "start": 3.4,
    "text": "And the kimchi is too, did I mention it?"
  },
  {
    "start": 5.4,
    "text": "Kamsamida!"
  },
  {
    "start": 6.6,
    "text": "Hello everybody! I am with a special guest today, my dad,"
  },
  {
    "start": 11.6,
    "text": "and we are ready to eat today."
  },
  {
    "start": 14.9,
    "text": "He will be trying out different kinds of Korean food that we got from a market here,"
  },
  {
    "start": 20.4,
    "text": "but actually he's already been to Korea."
  },
  {
    "start": 23.2,
    "text": "So do you really remember any of the Korean food that you've tried?"
  },
  {
    "start": 27.6,
    "text": "Korean barbecue. It was really, really good."
  },
  {
    "start": 29.9,
    "text": "And kimchi. I like kimchi."
  },
  {
    "start": 31.8,
    "text": "Those are probably the two most popular Korean foods."
  },
  {
    "start": 34.8,
    "text": "Does any of this look familiar to you?"
  },
  {
    "start": 37.0,
    "text": "It's completely new to me. It all smells really good."
  },
  {
    "start": 40.2,
    "text": "I might say. We've got the whole kitchen smelling good."
  },
  {
    "start": 43.2,
    "text": "We are going to start with this. This is called tapoki."
  },
  {
    "start": 47.0,
    "text": "Tapoki."
  },
  {
    "start": 47.8,
    "text": "Very good. That's perfect. Tapoki."
  },
  {
    "start": 49.7,
    "text": "If you were to just look at this, what would you guess that it is?"
  },
  {
    "start": 53.9,
    "text": "I would guess it's some type of noodles, cheese, and sauce."
  },
  {
    "start": 57.4,
    "text": "It looks good and it smells good."
  },
  {
    "start": 59.1,
    "text": "Yeah, it looks like a little milky kind of the little pasta."
  },
  {
    "start": 62.8,
    "text": "Yes."
  },
  {
    "start": 63.3,
    "text": "But it's actually rice cake."
  },
  {
    "start": 65.1,
    "text": "Usually it's super spicy."
  },
  {
    "start": 67.0,
    "text": "This one is cheese flavor, so it's a bit more mild."
  },
  {
    "start": 69.9,
    "text": "So we try."
  },
  {
    "start": 70.6,
    "text": "Let's give it a whirl."
  },
  {
    "start": 71.6,
    "text": "Again."
  },
  {
    "start": 75.8,
    "text": "Good taste."
  },
  {
    "start": 76.8,
    "text": "Good texture."
  },
  {
    "start": 78.2,
    "text": "Yummy."
  },
  {
    "start": 79.2,
    "text": "You like it?"
  },
  {
    "start": 79.8,
    "text": "I do."
  },
  {
    "start": 80.4,
    "text": "Okay."
  },
  {
    "start": 81.4,
    "text": "Sometimes they'll have fish cakes inside or I like it with ramen noodles."
  },
  {
    "start": 86.9,
    "text": "So they'll do different toppings and they'll also do different kinds of sauces."
  },
  {
    "start": 90.6,
    "text": "You may have another one."
  },
  {
    "start": 91.6,
    "text": "Of course."
  },
  {
    "start": 92.1,
    "text": "Eat as much as you like."
  },
  {
    "start": 93.6,
    "text": "It's really good."
  },
  {
    "start": 94.6,
    "text": "Really, really good."
  },
  {
    "start": 95.7,
    "text": "I like the sauce."
  },
  {
    "start": 96.7,
    "text": "You just got a little zip to it."
  },
  {
    "start": 98.5,
    "text": "Not bad, though."
  },
  {
    "start": 99.2,
    "text": "Not over the top."
  },
  {
    "start": 100.6,
    "text": "I like it."
  },
  {
    "start": 101.4,
    "text": "Mm-hmm."
  },
  {
    "start": 102.6,
    "text": "Two thumbs up."
  },
  {
    "start": 103.4,
    "text": "All right."
  },
  {
    "start": 104.5,
    "text": "So out of ten, what would you rate this?"
  },
  {
    "start": 107.4,
    "text": "A ten."
  },
  {
    "start": 108.2,
    "text": "Ooh, bulky fan."
  },
  {
    "start": 111.2,
    "text": "I like it because it's saucy, cheesy, chewy, gooey, yummy."
  },
  {
    "start": 116.4,
    "text": "Eat as much as you like."
  },
  {
    "start": 117.5,
    "text": "All right, Dan."
  },
  {
    "start": 119.4,
    "text": "Dan's the true test."
  },
  {
    "start": 123.1,
    "text": "She's a little pickier than my dad is."
  },
  {
    "start": 125.0,
    "text": "So she's the true test."
  },
  {
    "start": 126.5,
    "text": "Well, chewy."
  },
  {
    "start": 127.5,
    "text": "Mm-hmm."
  },
  {
    "start": 128.4,
    "text": "It's pretty good."
  },
  {
    "start": 129.4,
    "text": "Yeah, so I probably give it a maybe a eight."
  },
  {
    "start": 133.0,
    "text": "Okay."
  },
  {
    "start": 133.6,
    "text": "Hey, that's pretty good."
  },
  {
    "start": 135.0,
    "text": "So here we have shin ramen."
  },
  {
    "start": 138.0,
    "text": "We did about half of this spice packet."
  },
  {
    "start": 140.3,
    "text": "So it's not as spicy."
  },
  {
    "start": 141.7,
    "text": "Let me see if I can remember how to do this."
  },
  {
    "start": 143.7,
    "text": "They make a special bowl out of the wrapper here,"
  },
  {
    "start": 148.6,
    "text": "and then go ahead and try it, if you like."
  },
  {
    "start": 153.5,
    "text": "I need the bowl."
  },
  {
    "start": 154.5,
    "text": "I need the bowl."
  },
  {
    "start": 156.2,
    "text": "Wow."
  },
  {
    "start": 157.4,
    "text": "There you go."
  },
  {
    "start": 158.0,
    "text": "All right."
  },
  {
    "start": 160.7,
    "text": "You look Korean eating it like that."
  },
  {
    "start": 163.2,
    "text": "Very Korean style."
  },
  {
    "start": 166.3,
    "text": "Good."
  },
  {
    "start": 168.8,
    "text": "That's the way to do it."
  },
  {
    "start": 170.0,
    "text": "Like a shot."
  },
  {
    "start": 171.6,
    "text": "It's good."
  },
  {
    "start": 173.2,
    "text": "It is spicy."
  },
  {
    "start": 174.2,
    "text": "Mm-hmm."
  },
  {
    "start": 175.0,
    "text": "It clear your sinuses out, all right?"
  },
  {
    "start": 177.0,
    "text": "Uh-huh."
  },
  {
    "start": 177.4,
    "text": "This is very popular like when people go camping,"
  },
  {
    "start": 180.9,
    "text": "they'll have this in the morning for breakfast"
  },
  {
    "start": 183.1,
    "text": "after drinking a lot of beers or soju the night before."
  },
  {
    "start": 187.0,
    "text": "I don't know if I'd try it for breakfast."
  },
  {
    "start": 190.0,
    "text": "And I'm more traditional bacon, eggs, cereal,"
  },
  {
    "start": 193.9,
    "text": "but it's got a good taste to it."
  },
  {
    "start": 195.4,
    "text": "It's spicy."
  },
  {
    "start": 196.7,
    "text": "You just got a little bite to it."
  },
  {
    "start": 198.2,
    "text": "Yeah."
  },
  {
    "start": 198.8,
    "text": "So if you can take a small piece of the kimchi,"
  },
  {
    "start": 201.8,
    "text": "and then if you can get some noodles"
  },
  {
    "start": 204.2,
    "text": "to eat it together with this,"
  },
  {
    "start": 206.2,
    "text": "so kimchi is usually served as a side dish."
  },
  {
    "start": 209.6,
    "text": "So if you're eating noodles or rice,"
  },
  {
    "start": 212.9,
    "text": "you'll eat it together."
  },
  {
    "start": 213.9,
    "text": "Perfect."
  },
  {
    "start": 214.9,
    "text": "It's good."
  },
  {
    "start": 215.3,
    "text": "Down hatch."
  },
  {
    "start": 217.4,
    "text": "I love the kimchi."
  },
  {
    "start": 219.4,
    "text": "I like the vinegary,"
  },
  {
    "start": 221.2,
    "text": "picoli, and the texture."
  },
  {
    "start": 223.4,
    "text": "I can see why you'd eat it together."
  },
  {
    "start": 225.4,
    "text": "Kimchi is like the national dish of Korea."
  },
  {
    "start": 228.6,
    "text": "I like kimchi."
  },
  {
    "start": 229.6,
    "text": "Yeah?"
  },
  {
    "start": 230.3,
    "text": "Oh yeah."
  },
  {
    "start": 231.0,
    "text": "No, I'm the guy that'll drink pickle juice right out of the jar."
  },
  {
    "start": 235.6,
    "text": "And this resembles that a little bit."
  },
  {
    "start": 238.5,
    "text": "Wow, I can see where I get it from."
  },
  {
    "start": 239.8,
    "text": "I also drink pickle juice."
  },
  {
    "start": 241.3,
    "text": "Oh yeah."
  },
  {
    "start": 242.2,
    "text": "Yeah."
  },
  {
    "start": 242.8,
    "text": "Like father-like daughter,"
  },
  {
    "start": 244.2,
    "text": "what do you rate the shin ramen out of ten?"
  },
  {
    "start": 247.2,
    "text": "I mean, me personally,"
  },
  {
    "start": 248.3,
    "text": "I'm not a huge noodle guy."
  },
  {
    "start": 250.4,
    "text": "I'd go about eight on it."
  },
  {
    "start": 252.3,
    "text": "How about the kimchi?"
  },
  {
    "start": 254.0,
    "text": "11."
  },
  {
    "start": 254.8,
    "text": "Oh!"
  },
  {
    "start": 256.2,
    "text": "I love this."
  },
  {
    "start": 257.6,
    "text": "I do this."
  },
  {
    "start": 258.3,
    "text": "I could make a meal out of this."
  },
  {
    "start": 260.2,
    "text": "This is black bean."
  },
  {
    "start": 263.0,
    "text": "Black bean noodle."
  },
  {
    "start": 264.2,
    "text": "It's called chapegetti."
  },
  {
    "start": 266.2,
    "text": "Chapegetti."
  },
  {
    "start": 267.8,
    "text": "Chapegetti."
  },
  {
    "start": 270.8,
    "text": "Does it remind you of anything in the flavor?"
  },
  {
    "start": 273.4,
    "text": "Um, I gotta have one more bite to make sure."
  },
  {
    "start": 276.6,
    "text": "Just to make sure it's got its own unique taste."
  },
  {
    "start": 280.6,
    "text": "I'm trying to associate it with something"
  },
  {
    "start": 282.7,
    "text": "that I'm used to, but nothing's coming to mind."
  },
  {
    "start": 284.9,
    "text": "It's good."
  },
  {
    "start": 285.5,
    "text": "It's a mild mellow."
  },
  {
    "start": 287.5,
    "text": "Which do you prefer?"
  },
  {
    "start": 288.6,
    "text": "Do you think the shin ramen or the chapegetti"
  },
  {
    "start": 291.4,
    "text": "if you had to choose?"
  },
  {
    "start": 292.8,
    "text": "If I had to choose, I'd say the shin ramen."
  },
  {
    "start": 295.1,
    "text": "I'm a shin girl, too."
  },
  {
    "start": 296.4,
    "text": "Yeah."
  },
  {
    "start": 297.4,
    "text": "Only because I think that has more spices"
  },
  {
    "start": 300.2,
    "text": "for this is a little more not so spicy, I guess."
  },
  {
    "start": 303.2,
    "text": "I agree."
  },
  {
    "start": 303.7,
    "text": "This is more flavorful."
  },
  {
    "start": 305.1,
    "text": "Yeah."
  },
  {
    "start": 305.5,
    "text": "Yep."
  },
  {
    "start": 305.9,
    "text": "This is kind of bland."
  },
  {
    "start": 307.7,
    "text": "In a way, I'm starting to say that."
  },
  {
    "start": 310.2,
    "text": "I better try another piece of kimchi with it."
  },
  {
    "start": 312.6,
    "text": "There you go."
  },
  {
    "start": 315.5,
    "text": "You dig the kimchi, huh?"
  },
  {
    "start": 316.5,
    "text": "Mm-hmm."
  },
  {
    "start": 317.3,
    "text": "All right, so what would you rate the chapegetti?"
  },
  {
    "start": 320.6,
    "text": "I'm going to say six,"
  },
  {
    "start": 322.2,
    "text": "only because I guess I'm more of a spicy eater?"
  },
  {
    "start": 325.4,
    "text": "Yep."
  },
  {
    "start": 325.9,
    "text": "So this is called hit bun."
  },
  {
    "start": 328.6,
    "text": "Say it again."
  },
  {
    "start": 329.4,
    "text": "Hit bun."
  },
  {
    "start": 330.7,
    "text": "Hit bun."
  },
  {
    "start": 331.4,
    "text": "Yep, hit bun."
  },
  {
    "start": 332.6,
    "text": "And this is just a microwave rice,"
  },
  {
    "start": 335.5,
    "text": "but what's kind of unique about Korean rice"
  },
  {
    "start": 337.8,
    "text": "is that it's very sticky."
  },
  {
    "start": 339.4,
    "text": "You can do a meal where it's rice"
  },
  {
    "start": 342.0,
    "text": "and then kimchi and a lot of other small side dishes in stew."
  },
  {
    "start": 346.2,
    "text": "You guys took me to a restaurant"
  },
  {
    "start": 347.8,
    "text": "and that sounds a lot like what we had."
  },
  {
    "start": 349.9,
    "text": "That night was rice, kimchi,"
  },
  {
    "start": 352.6,
    "text": "and that lady brought up different little sides."
  },
  {
    "start": 356.4,
    "text": "Yeah."
  },
  {
    "start": 356.9,
    "text": "And usually the good thing about the sides"
  },
  {
    "start": 359.5,
    "text": "is you get free refills."
  },
  {
    "start": 361.5,
    "text": "Oh."
  },
  {
    "start": 363.1,
    "text": "So if you like the side dish, you can say,"
  },
  {
    "start": 365.4,
    "text": "keep it coming."
  },
  {
    "start": 366.2,
    "text": "I thought she just liked me."
  },
  {
    "start": 369.1,
    "text": "That's like that for everyone."
  },
  {
    "start": 370.6,
    "text": "She did."
  },
  {
    "start": 371.4,
    "text": "It was only for you."
  },
  {
    "start": 374.2,
    "text": "I'd have to have some of this with it."
  },
  {
    "start": 375.9,
    "text": "Mm-hmm."
  },
  {
    "start": 376.6,
    "text": "You know, they'll have some kind of soup or stew"
  },
  {
    "start": 379.0,
    "text": "and they'll take a spoonful of the rice and some broth."
  },
  {
    "start": 382.4,
    "text": "I would have to have something with that."
  },
  {
    "start": 384.6,
    "text": "Right."
  },
  {
    "start": 385.4,
    "text": "Otherwise it's kind of plain by itself."
  },
  {
    "start": 387.8,
    "text": "And that's usually how it's eaten."
  },
  {
    "start": 389.3,
    "text": "Okay."
  },
  {
    "start": 389.6,
    "text": "Most people won't eat this just plain."
  },
  {
    "start": 391.5,
    "text": "Okay."
  },
  {
    "start": 392.2,
    "text": "It feels like it's thoroughly cooked,"
  },
  {
    "start": 393.9,
    "text": "but it's not undercooked."
  },
  {
    "start": 396.2,
    "text": "It's not crunchy."
  },
  {
    "start": 397.3,
    "text": "Right."
  },
  {
    "start": 397.7,
    "text": "You know, and it's not soggy."
  },
  {
    "start": 399.7,
    "text": "Right."
  },
  {
    "start": 400.0,
    "text": "It's right there in the middle."
  },
  {
    "start": 401.1,
    "text": "I'd probably give it an eight"
  },
  {
    "start": 403.0,
    "text": "because of the way it breaks apart so nicely and evenly."
  },
  {
    "start": 405.9,
    "text": "Mm-hmm."
  },
  {
    "start": 406.6,
    "text": "Um, I'd give it a ten if I could mix it with this or that."
  },
  {
    "start": 410.0,
    "text": "Then I'll say you'll give it a ten"
  },
  {
    "start": 411.5,
    "text": "because that's usually how you eat it."
  },
  {
    "start": 413.4,
    "text": "Okay."
  },
  {
    "start": 413.9,
    "text": "I like the texture of it."
  },
  {
    "start": 415.2,
    "text": "I feel like this is a very beloved Korean food,"
  },
  {
    "start": 418.3,
    "text": "especially among Americans in other foreigners."
  },
  {
    "start": 421.7,
    "text": "So this is mandu."
  },
  {
    "start": 423.6,
    "text": "In mandu is just a dumpling."
  },
  {
    "start": 426.5,
    "text": "So there is meat and vegetables inside of here."
  },
  {
    "start": 430.5,
    "text": "Ooh."
  },
  {
    "start": 431.1,
    "text": "Yeah."
  },
  {
    "start": 434.6,
    "text": "I like it."
  },
  {
    "start": 435.3,
    "text": "Mm-hmm."
  },
  {
    "start": 436.2,
    "text": "It's got a crispy, low shell, moist inside,"
  },
  {
    "start": 441.2,
    "text": "flavorful."
  },
  {
    "start": 442.4,
    "text": "What did you say is inside this particular one?"
  },
  {
    "start": 444.8,
    "text": "Beef and vegetables."
  },
  {
    "start": 447.6,
    "text": "All kind of ground up."
  },
  {
    "start": 449.0,
    "text": "Yep."
  },
  {
    "start": 449.3,
    "text": "You can have them steamed,"
  },
  {
    "start": 450.8,
    "text": "so it's not crispy,"
  },
  {
    "start": 451.8,
    "text": "but it's soft on the outside"
  },
  {
    "start": 453.8,
    "text": "and you can get them fried."
  },
  {
    "start": 455.7,
    "text": "Usually it's served with some kind of dipping sauce,"
  },
  {
    "start": 459.1,
    "text": "similar to soy sauce."
  },
  {
    "start": 460.5,
    "text": "You can add kimchi with it?"
  },
  {
    "start": 461.8,
    "text": "Yeah."
  },
  {
    "start": 463.0,
    "text": "I see the greens in there for the vegetables."
  },
  {
    "start": 465.8,
    "text": "We're eating healthy."
  },
  {
    "start": 468.2,
    "text": "I see you dip yours in that."
  },
  {
    "start": 469.4,
    "text": "Yeah, I see it's good."
  },
  {
    "start": 470.4,
    "text": "It's a little world."
  },
  {
    "start": 471.2,
    "text": "Yep."
  },
  {
    "start": 471.7,
    "text": "Because that sauce is really good."
  },
  {
    "start": 473.4,
    "text": "Mm-hmm."
  },
  {
    "start": 473.7,
    "text": "It's yummy."
  },
  {
    "start": 474.3,
    "text": "And the kimchi is too, did I mention it?"
  },
  {
    "start": 476.6,
    "text": "I don't think you said that."
  },
  {
    "start": 479.4,
    "text": "Probably my go-to Korean foods."
  },
  {
    "start": 482.2,
    "text": "If I can't decide what to eat"
  },
  {
    "start": 484.1,
    "text": "or if nothing sounds good,"
  },
  {
    "start": 485.8,
    "text": "dumpling always does the trick."
  },
  {
    "start": 487.5,
    "text": "I see why."
  },
  {
    "start": 488.4,
    "text": "Yeah."
  },
  {
    "start": 489.0,
    "text": "What would you rate these out of?"
  },
  {
    "start": 491.3,
    "text": "10."
  },
  {
    "start": 491.8,
    "text": "10."
  },
  {
    "start": 492.5,
    "text": "Oh yeah."
  },
  {
    "start": 493.3,
    "text": "A quick and easy 10."
  },
  {
    "start": 494.3,
    "text": "Yep."
  },
  {
    "start": 494.9,
    "text": "I could eat those for a meal"
  },
  {
    "start": 497.0,
    "text": "or an order."
  },
  {
    "start": 498.9,
    "text": "She likes that stuff."
  },
  {
    "start": 500.9,
    "text": "Yeah, you go."
  },
  {
    "start": 501.7,
    "text": "I like the mandu."
  },
  {
    "start": 502.8,
    "text": "And you can have them with kimchi."
  },
  {
    "start": 505.7,
    "text": "Kimchi goes with everything."
  },
  {
    "start": 507.4,
    "text": "We always got to finish with a dessert."
  },
  {
    "start": 509.0,
    "text": "One of my favorite times."
  },
  {
    "start": 511.4,
    "text": "So this is a traditional Korean street food"
  },
  {
    "start": 515.6,
    "text": "called boomapang."
  },
  {
    "start": 517.0,
    "text": "Boomapang."
  },
  {
    "start": 518.0,
    "text": "And it's a dessert?"
  },
  {
    "start": 519.0,
    "text": "It's a dessert."
  },
  {
    "start": 519.9,
    "text": "In Korea, they have sugar mixed with the red bean"
  },
  {
    "start": 522.9,
    "text": "and they use it for a lot of desserts."
  },
  {
    "start": 525.0,
    "text": "But you can also get it filled with cream."
  },
  {
    "start": 527.8,
    "text": "But this is the traditional one."
  },
  {
    "start": 529.8,
    "text": "Okay."
  },
  {
    "start": 530.5,
    "text": "And we call the red bean pot."
  },
  {
    "start": 532.2,
    "text": "Pot."
  },
  {
    "start": 532.7,
    "text": "So pot means red bean, so."
  },
  {
    "start": 534.5,
    "text": "Red bean."
  },
  {
    "start": 535.2,
    "text": "Cheers."
  },
  {
    "start": 539.1,
    "text": "Who would have ever thought red bean would be a dessert?"
  },
  {
    "start": 542.0,
    "text": "I know."
  },
  {
    "start": 542.5,
    "text": "Very different than American dessert."
  },
  {
    "start": 544.6,
    "text": "It tastes really sweet."
  },
  {
    "start": 545.8,
    "text": "I like it because it is red bean"
  },
  {
    "start": 547.8,
    "text": "it's not like gelatin, jelly stuffed in there."
  },
  {
    "start": 551.4,
    "text": "This seems more natural."
  },
  {
    "start": 553.5,
    "text": "When you think of this versus traditional American dessert,"
  },
  {
    "start": 558.4,
    "text": "what kind of differences would you notice or think of?"
  },
  {
    "start": 561.9,
    "text": "I like this because you almost feel like you're eating a pastry."
  },
  {
    "start": 565.6,
    "text": "A warm hot pastry."
  },
  {
    "start": 567.0,
    "text": "Would you say it's as sweet as most American desserts or?"
  },
  {
    "start": 570.6,
    "text": "It depends on what."
  },
  {
    "start": 571.4,
    "text": "Americans are nuts with sweets."
  },
  {
    "start": 574.3,
    "text": "Like a brownie or cookies."
  },
  {
    "start": 576.1,
    "text": "Right."
  },
  {
    "start": 576.5,
    "text": "Some cookies are sweeter,"
  },
  {
    "start": 577.8,
    "text": "but this is like the perfect level of sweetness."
  },
  {
    "start": 581.2,
    "text": "I think."
  },
  {
    "start": 581.9,
    "text": "This is very popular in the winter time."
  },
  {
    "start": 583.9,
    "text": "It's a winter street food snack."
  },
  {
    "start": 586.1,
    "text": "We're eating 12 of them being not good."
  },
  {
    "start": 590.1,
    "text": "I feel like I'm on a grave."
  },
  {
    "start": 591.4,
    "text": "You know, six, eight, 10 of them or something."
  },
  {
    "start": 593.6,
    "text": "Usually they are this big."
  },
  {
    "start": 595.4,
    "text": "So it's full pastry size."
  },
  {
    "start": 597.2,
    "text": "These ones are many ones."
  },
  {
    "start": 598.4,
    "text": "I could see me knocking off a half dozen to a dozen of those"
  },
  {
    "start": 601.9,
    "text": "with a little bit of chocolate milk and then a coffee or something."
  },
  {
    "start": 605.8,
    "text": "How about your rating for this?"
  },
  {
    "start": 607.8,
    "text": "I'd say a 10."
  },
  {
    "start": 608.7,
    "text": "Yeah."
  },
  {
    "start": 609.9,
    "text": "Everything I've tried here today,"
  },
  {
    "start": 611.4,
    "text": "maybe it's because it's all new to me,"
  },
  {
    "start": 613.2,
    "text": "but it all tastes good."
  },
  {
    "start": 615.4,
    "text": "So you're a fan of Korean food then?"
  },
  {
    "start": 617.4,
    "text": "Yeah."
  },
  {
    "start": 617.8,
    "text": "You get this mental thing in your head."
  },
  {
    "start": 619.8,
    "text": "Korean food, we're going to eat rice and that's it."
  },
  {
    "start": 623.4,
    "text": "This is creative Korean food and it's tasty."
  },
  {
    "start": 628.6,
    "text": "I think Korea has so many dishes,"
  },
  {
    "start": 630.9,
    "text": "like even I haven't tried half of them probably."
  },
  {
    "start": 634.3,
    "text": "Everything I've tried here is phenomenal."
  },
  {
    "start": 636.7,
    "text": "Do you think I should open a tapoki shop"
  },
  {
    "start": 639.1,
    "text": "or bunga pung stand in Saginaw?"
  },
  {
    "start": 641.4,
    "text": "I think it might do go all right."
  },
  {
    "start": 642.9,
    "text": "All right."
  },
  {
    "start": 643.5,
    "text": "Next business venture."
  },
  {
    "start": 644.9,
    "text": "I think so."
  },
  {
    "start": 645.5,
    "text": "So out of everything,"
  },
  {
    "start": 647.6,
    "text": "I know it's hard,"
  },
  {
    "start": 648.5,
    "text": "but if you could only choose one food,"
  },
  {
    "start": 651.4,
    "text": "what would you say was your favorite?"
  },
  {
    "start": 655.8,
    "text": "No hesitation."
  },
  {
    "start": 657.3,
    "text": "Well, I definitely like the kimchi,"
  },
  {
    "start": 659.4,
    "text": "but I really like this."
  },
  {
    "start": 661.0,
    "text": "I really like mandu."
  },
  {
    "start": 663.1,
    "text": "I really like this."
  },
  {
    "start": 665.0,
    "text": "I like everything."
  },
  {
    "start": 666.1,
    "text": "I've tried so far."
  },
  {
    "start": 667.4,
    "text": "But kimchi's top."
  },
  {
    "start": 668.8,
    "text": "Absolutely."
  },
  {
    "start": 669.5,
    "text": "Yeah, I appreciate you."
  },
  {
    "start": 671.8,
    "text": "Have me taste test all this."
  },
  {
    "start": 673.7,
    "text": "We got it anymore."
  },
  {
    "start": 675.6,
    "text": "This was a lot of instant food,"
  },
  {
    "start": 678.2,
    "text": "but next time we'll cook some real Korean dinner."
  },
  {
    "start": 682.2,
    "text": "I appreciate you doing this today."
  },
  {
    "start": 684.2,
    "text": "So that's the end of our Korean mukbang today."
  },
  {
    "start": 688.1,
    "text": "Seems my dad enjoyed the food."
  },
  {
    "start": 689.9,
    "text": "If you want to take your English to the next level,"
  },
  {
    "start": 693.7,
    "text": "check out our membership option."
  },
  {
    "start": 695.8,
    "text": "See you next time, guys."
  },
  {
    "start": 697.4,
    "text": "Bye."
  },
  {
    "start": 698.2,
    "text": "Thank you."
  },
  {
    "start": 699.4,
    "text": "Thank you."
  }
]